<div class="xl-row xl-middle xl-vjustify">
	<div class="fill-1 col middle justify shaded">
		<div class="col content gap-4">
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>The Schedule</h3>
				<p><strong>On Friday April 8th:</strong> Hackers arrive between <strong>7pm and 9pm</strong>. The opening ceremony begins at <strong>9pm</strong>, and coding begins at <strong>10pm</strong>.</p>
				<p><strong>On Sunday April 10th:</strong> Coding stops at <strong>9am</strong>. We'll announce winners and have people back on buses by <strong>2pm</strong>.</p>
				<p>We'll post a more detailed schedule shortly.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Packing List</h3>
				<p>CarlHacks is completely free to attend. You'll need <strong>a laptop, charger, and student ID</strong>. We'd also recommend bringing <strong>toiletries, shower shoes, a change of clothing, and a pillow</strong>. We'll provide meals, snacks, showers, and air beds for napping. If you don't have a project idea or team, don't worry! There will be team-forming events, and we find some of our best ideas come <em>during</em> the hackathon, not before. If you come with a team, note that the maximum team size is five.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Join Us</h3>
				<div class="col left"><tito-button event="carlhacks/2016" class="button-light button-disabled">Registration Closed</tito-button></div>
				<p>Shoot us an email at <a href="mailto:team@carlhacks.com">team@carlhacks.com</a> if you have any questions, disabilities, special needs, or if there's anything else we can do to ensure CarlHacks goes smoothly for you. This is an MLH event, so we abide by the <a href="/pdf/coc.pdf">MLH code of conduct</a>.</p>
				<p>If you're a Carleton student and haven't registered yet, you can email us to get a ticket.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="fill-1 shaded-dark col">
		<img class="full-img" src="/images/rec.jpg">
		<div class="col content gap-4">
			<div class="col justify vjustify gap-3">
				<h3>Traveling to CarlHacks</h3>
				<p>CarlHacks is hosted in Northfield, Minnesota, at Carleton College's Recreation Center. If you're not already in Northfield, there are plenty of ways to get here.</p>
				<ul class="col gap-2">
					<li><p><strong>By Bus</strong> &mdash; We have buses picking up hackers from schools near the Twin Cities.</p></li>
					<li><p><strong>By Car</strong> &mdash; You're welcome to drive over! We're located at <a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Recreation+Center/@44.4658458,-93.1509383,17z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x87f653b24725124b:0x6d95c2df8da47350!2s501+Three+Oaks+Dr,+Northfield,+MN+55057!3b1!3m1!1s0x0000000000000000:0x5b430ae20b614ef7?hl=en" class="light-link">501 Three Oaks Drive, Northfield, MN</a>. There's plenty of parking available near the back entrance of the building, next to the water tower in the image above.</p></li>
				</ul>
				<p>If you have any concerns or questions about travel, we're here to help! Shoot us an email at <a href="mailto:team@carlhacks.com">team@carlhacks.com</a>.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
